Let $X = x_1 \ldots x_n$ with $n \ge 4$ and $x_i \in \Sigma$ (token vocabulary). The final token $x_n$ is the query token $q$.\nIn the context $x_1 \ldots x_{n-1}$, $q$ appears $t$ times at indices $q_1, \ldots, q_t$ ($1 \le q_1 \le q_t \le n-1$).\n\nContinuation token $x_{n+1}$ is defined by:\n$t = 1$ and $x_{n+1} = x_{q_1-1}$\n\nExample - \n 1 q r j R | j: r
• query token = “j” (everything after “|”)
